# LazbbComponents package<br>

[Vers page du paquet en Français](https://github.com/bb84000/Lazbbcomponents/wiki/Controls_fr)<br>

Extra components with properties unavailable in Lazarus/FPC native components  

**TCheckBoxX** : Multifunction check box: colored square, cross, check mark, image.<br>
**TColorPicker** : Colors choice similar to Components inspector (Colors combo box plus colors dialog button)<br>
**TSCrollButton** : Text scrolling button (TSpeedbutton descendant)<br>
**TSCrollLabel** : Text scrolling label (TLabel descendant)<br>
**TSignalMeter** : A more responsive progress bar, allow real time audio signal strength<br>
**TLFPTimer** : FPTimer component<br> 
**TitlePanel** : Panel with a title like a GroupBox. Can change border color and title alignment<br>
**TbbTrackBar** : A customizable trackbar. Slider, ruler and scale colors can be changed<br>
**TbbOneInst** : Prevents execution of a second instance of the application (can use a command line parameter to allow different instances to run).<br>
**TbbOsVersion** : Retrieve OS version and information. Replace lazbosver unit.

### TCheckBoxX; properties

  **CheckBoxType** : square, cross, check, image.<br>
  **CheckboxColor** (Tcolor) : check square color
 
### TcolorPicker properties

  Base colors, and their identifiers cannot be changed. Selected text cannot be edited. To change the selected color, use the colors dialog or paste a color with the popup menu.<br>
  An invalid color is ignored. Selected colours not in base colours are added at the end of the list. Like base combo box, component height is related to the items height.<br>
  The colors dialog is localized by the operating system.

  **Color** (TColor): Initial color<br>
  **MnuCopyCaption**, **MnuPasteCaption** (String): allow popup localization

### TSCrollButton and TScrollLabel properties

  **Scrolling** (True or false): Enable or disable caption scrolling. 
            When caption is shorter than button width, scrolling is always disabled. 
			Default: scrolling is not enabled.<br>
  **ScrollInterval** (ms): Set the scroolling speed. A low interval means a high scrolling speed. 
            A too low value doesn(t allow a smooth scrolling as the processor cannot do its job in the interval. 
			Default : 50 ms.<br>
  **ScrollAutoString** (string): String added at the end of the text during scrolling. Default is '...'<br> 
  **ScrollGraph** (True or false): Enable graphic (smooth) scrolling (pixel by pixel instead text scrolling 
            (character by character). Default: graphic.<br>
  **ScrollStep** (number): Scrolling step (character or pixel according scrolling mode). Default 1.<br>
  **ScrollDirection** : Scrolling direction, left to right or right to left. Default : left to right. 

### TitlePanel properties

  **Alignment** : Title position on the box : Left, right or center <br>
  **BorderColor** (Tcolor) : Color of the box border
  
### TbbTrackBar properties

  **SliderColor** : Slider default color<br>
  **SliderColorDown** : Slider color on mouse button down<br>
  **SliderColorHover** : Slider color on mouse cursor over<br>
  **SliderBorderColor** Slider border color<br>
  **SliderStyle** : ssClassic: same as TTrackBar; ssButton: button like slider<br>
  **Slidersize** : Slider's thickness. Slider width/height is always 21 pixels<br>
  **RulerColor** : Ruler color<br>
  **RulerBorderColor** : Ruler border color<br>
  **RulerSize** : Ruler thickness<br>
  **ScaleMarks** : Same as TTrackbar TickMark<br>
  **ScaleSize** : Min, max and zero scale ticks size. Other ticks are half size<br>
  **ScaleColor** Couleur des divisions de l'échelle<br>
  **Frequency** Divider for the scale ticks, also used as position step move when pgUp nd PgDn keys pressed<br>
  **KeyIncrement** : Position step move when arrow key pressed. Home key pressed set position to Min, End key pressed set position to Max 

### TbbOneInst properties

  **Enabled** : Determines whether the componet is active or not<br>
  **Identifier** : A unique string defining the application. Use a GUID to be sure no other application can have the same identifier. 
                   If no identifier is provided, the executable name is used..<br>
  **Useparameter** : Allow simultaneous execution of the same application whith differeent command line parameters.<br>
  **UpdateInterval** : With non-windows OS, polling interval to retreive message from second instance.<br>
  **OnOtherInstance** : Event fired by the component when a second instance is launched.<br>
  _TbbOneInst uses part of **UniqueInstance** component code développed by [Luiz Américo Pereira Câmara](https://wiki.freepascal.org/User:Luizmed)_
  
### TbbOsVersion properties, variables and procedure 
  
  ### _Properties_

  **OSName** : Operating system name (read-only).<br>
  **Architecture** : Processor architecture (read-only).<br>
  **VerDetail** : OS description, with version, build etc. (read-only).<br>
  _Windows only properties_<br>
  **ProdStrs** : Product type list, editable to update and/or translate<br>
  **Win10Strs** : Windows 10 versions descriptions list, editable to update and/or translate<br>
  **Win11Strs** : Windows 11 versions descriptions list, editable to update and/or translate<br>
  **VerMaj** :  Major version number (read-only)<br>
  **VerMin** : Minor version number (read-only)<br>
  **VerBuild** : Build number (read-only)<br>
  **VerSup** : Additional version information (read-only)<br>
  **VerMask** : Product suite mask (read-only)<br>
  **VerTyp** : Windows type (read-only)<br>
  **VerProd** : Version type (read-only)<br>
  _Linux, Unix or MacOs only properties_<br>
  **KernelName** : OS kernel name (read-only)<br>
  **KernelRelease** : OS kernel release (read-only)<br>
  **KernelVersion** : OS kernel version (read-only)<br>
  **NetworkNode** : Network node name (read-only)<br>
   
  ### _Procedure_
  
  **GetSysInfo** : Reset OS info detection

Free to use

